<main class="ww-main">

  <header class="ww-page-header">
    <div>
      <h1>Attendance</h1>
      <p class="ww-subtitle">
        Track who’s attending ward meetings. Members can scan a QR code to check in.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ww-header-actions">
      <!-- Simple link back to the member directory (GET /members) -->
      <a href="/members" class="ww-btn ww-btn-secondary">
        ← Back to Directory
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="ww-card">
    <h2>How QR Check-In Works</h2>

    <ol class="ww-list">
      <li>Leaders display a QR code in sacrament meeting or class.</li>

      <li>Members log in on their phone and scan the code.</li>

      <li>
        <!-- 
          This explains how the system uses the /attendance/checkin route.
          That route is handled by attendanceController.showCheckin(),
          which loads the member and shows their current status.
        -->
        The link goes to <code>/attendance/checkin</code>, and the system marks them
        present for today.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
      For testing, while logged in, you can click this link directly:
    </p>

    <!-- 
      This link triggers the GET /attendance/checkin route.
      If the logged-in user has a linked Member record,
      attendanceController.showCheckin() displays a check-in page.
    -->
    <p>
      <a href="/attendance/checkin" class="ww-btn ww-btn-primary">
        Test Check-In
      </a>
    </p>

  </section>

</main>
